  <div id="grooming" class="scroll-mt-40">
    <CaptionedBlock heading="Grooming: Silk Wants a Comb, Not a Salon" imageAlt="Silky Terrier puppy having its long coat combed through" imageSrc={imgScene3} imagePosition="left">
      <p>The Silky coat behaves like the Yorkie's: barely sheds, happily tangles. Most Singapore Silkies live in a practical trimmed cut, which brings the routine down to a comb-through 2 to 3 times a week and a tidy-up trim every 6 to 8 weeks. Kept long, upgrade to daily combing; the silk mats quietly if ignored.</p>
      <p>No undercoat means no coat blows and quick drying after rainy walks, both blessings here. The daily ten-second habits are the toy-breed standards: eye area check and tooth-brushing, with everything needed in your starter kit.</p>
    </CaptionedBlock>
  </div>

  <CloudDivider fillClass="fill-[var(--color-mint-100)]" />
  <div id="health" class="scroll-mt-40">
    <CaptionedBlock heading="Silky Terrier Health: What We Check Before You Take One Home" imageAlt="Silky Terrier puppy at a veterinary health check before going home" imageSrc={imgScene4} variant="mid">
      <p>Every Silky goes home vet-checked, vaccinated, dewormed, and microchipped. The breed is robust, working-terrier roots again, with a short list worth knowing: patellar luxation, the small-breed kneecap issue; dental crowding, met with the day-one brushing habit; tracheal sensitivity, which is why the harness rule applies; and Legg-Calvé-Perthes in some lines, as with most small terriers.</p>
      <p>Feeding is simple: your puppy comes with the food it is already eating, and any change should be gradual over a week. See the <a href="/learn/puppy-health" class="underline underline-offset-2 text-[var(--color-accent-hover)]">puppy health checks explained</a> guide.</p>
    </CaptionedBlock>
  </div>
  <CloudDivider fillClass="fill-[var(--color-mint-100)]" flip />

  <CaptionedBlock heading="Your Silky's First Week at Home" imageAlt="Silky Terrier puppy settling into a set-up playpen during its first week home" imageSrc={imgScene5} imagePosition="left">
    <p>Day 0: we deliver, free, at a time that suits you, usually morning or evening. The playpen, bed, water, and toys are set up before your Silky explores the room, and we walk you through all 30+ starter-kit items in person. Learn more about <a href="/delivery" class="underline underline-offset-2 text-[var(--color-accent-hover)]">how our free home delivery and setup works</a>.</p>
    <p>Days 1 to 3: keep it calm and predictable. A fixed feeding routine, the toilet pads where we placed them, and short, structured play; the terrier curiosity will want to inspect everything, so supervise the first explorations.</p>
    <p>Days 4 to 7: the routine sticks and the spark shows. Book your free first lesson with an AVS-certified trainer this week; the voice and the leash manners are best shaped now. See <a href="/free-training" class="underline underline-offset-2 text-[var(--color-accent-hover)]">what the free AVS-certified training lesson covers</a>.</p>
  </CaptionedBlock>

